# Complete platforms for the per-arch image PEXes, generated by `pex3 interpreter inspect --markers --tags`
# in a docker python:3.14-slim container per linux arch. Regenerate whenever the interpreter version changes
# — hand-copied subsets miss generic tags (py3-none-any) and break pure-python wheel resolution.
# https://www.pantsbuild.org/stable/docs/python/overview/pex#generating-the-complete_platforms-file
# The musl-linux-* (Alpine) JSONs are kept for reference but unused: numba + llvmlite (via beets) ship no
# cp314 musl wheel. macOS isn't targeted at all (the images are linux-only).

file(name="linux-aarch64", source="linux-aarch64.json")
file(name="linux-amd64", source="linux-amd64.json")
target(name="platforms", dependencies=[":linux-aarch64", ":linux-amd64"], tags=["complete-platforms"])
